(Using the equality comparison operator on numbers)

Int is 42
Float is 12.34
NegativeInt is -42
NegativeFloat is -12.34
ZeroInt is 0
ZeroFloat is 0.0

Say "numbers can equal booleans"
Rightness is right
Wrongness is wrong
say Int is Rightness
say Int is Wrongness
say Float is Rightness
say Float is Wrongness
say NegativeInt is Rightness
say NegativeInt is Wrongness
say NegativeFloat is Rightness
say NegativeFloat is Wrongness
say ZeroInt is Rightness
say ZeroInt is Wrongness
say ZeroFloat is Rightness
say ZeroFloat is Wrongness
say true is 42
say true is -42
say true is -0
say true is -0.0
say false is 42
say false is -42
say false is -0
say false is -0.0

Say "integers equal themselves"
say Int is Int
say NegativeInt is NegativeInt
say ZeroInt is ZeroInt
say Int is ZeroInt
say NegativeInt is ZeroInt
say 42 is 42
say -42 is -42
say -0 is ZeroInt

Say "floats equal themselves"
say Float is Float
say NegativeFloat is NegativeFloat
say ZeroFloat is ZeroFloat
say Float is ZeroFloat
say NegativeFloat is ZeroFloat
say 12.34 is 12.34
say -12.34 is -12.34
say -0.0 is ZeroFloat

Say "integers can equal floats"
say Int is 042.00
say NegativeInt is -042.00
say Int is 43.0
say 0 is ZeroFloat
say 0.0 is ZeroInt
say -0 is ZeroFloat
say -0.0 is ZeroInt
say 43.0 is 42

